Commentary Text: Thakur to Conway, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Chepauk silenced!! That's what could happen if you throw the ball to Shardul more often. Commentary Text: Chakaravarthy to Rahane, out Caught by Roy!! Gone! Chakaravarthy strikes again. Rahane had to take his chance because it was going to be a spin barrage from now on... Charges to the pitch and tries to go over long-on. However, the ball was darted a bit quicker and that meant Rahane couldn't get fully under it. Holes out to long-on. Commentary Text: Pathirana to Rinku Singh, out Rinku Singh Run Out!! Direct hit from Moeen and Rinku might be in trouble. He taps this to short cover, takes off for a single but is comfortably short of his ground. He'd be very disappointed to give his wicket away in this manner, but what a superb knock though. Came in at 33/3, team in trouble, sluggish pitch. And has almost finished the job along with his captain. Rinku Singh run out (Moeen Ali) 54(43) [4s-4 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Roy, out Caught by Pathirana!! Oh that's another outside edge that goes to short third man. Roy can't believe his luck. He smiles. Deepak Chahar smiles too. Commentary Text: Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Jadeja!! Edged and gone! How often do you see an edge go to short third man and not slip. Dhoni had no slip and this edge went where he put the fielder. Even short third was finer than normal. So Chahar has yet again got two wickets in the powerplay here. He does drag the ball back this time to bowl into the wicket, Venky goes for the cut shot but gets a thick edge that Jadeja swallows. Venkatesh Iyer c Jadeja b Chahar 9(4) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Gurbaz, out Caught by Tushar Deshpande!! Gurbaz, Gurbaz! That was a hit me ball and he's hit it to hand. He stands there in disbelief. He doesn't want to go. You can understand that disappointment. Full and wide outside off stump, proper dangling the carrot there from Chahar, Gurbaz slices it completely as he looks to drive. Tushar had distance to cover to the right, but he had his eyes on the ball and judged it to perfection. Also ensured he didn't trip onto the boundary rope. Great catch that. This is almost similar to Rohit's dismissal in Mohalli to a wide ball. Gurbaz c Tushar Deshpande b Chahar 1(4)
